Title: Awesome Digital Camera!
Cons: Kodak is going out of this business.  Too bad, this is one heck of a camera they made, and probably this review will not matter much since they probably do not make this camera anymore.  But they broke the mold on this one.
Pros:
1) So many features on small handheld digital camera
2) Better than I expected
3) Takes great movie pictures and still pictures, numerous digital size options to pick from
4) So compact and ideal to carry on travel
5) Durable and built well
6) No problems at all after 4 plus years of heavy use traveling all over the world with it.

Title: Excellent pictures for the cost
Cons: Sometimes does not turn back on immeadiatly after being turned off.  Had to pull the batteries and put back in to get it to come on.
Pros: Small, portable, lightweight.  Takes excellent pictures for the cost.
Comments: I haven't had the issue with the powering back on in a long time *knock on wood*.  Then again, I was using the batteries it came with which were some unknown brand.  I put in NiMh batteries and haven't had the issue since.

Title: Easy to Use
Cons: None yet
Pros: Very easy to use, True-to-life pictures indoors. Haven't tries it outdoors yet.

Title: Battery Hungry Bargin
Cons: Stock up on battries because you will need them, this puppy eats them like candy.
Pros: Great photos and features yet easy to use
Comments: Catch it on sale and it isn't a bad deal for a 9.2 MegPix camera.  Newegg is always great to deal with

Title: Great buy for the price
Cons: The build quality is a bit poor. Feels like you're holding a toy camera. The LCD quality in preview mode is poor, but does not resemble to image quality.
Pros: I purchased this camera as a gift for my mother, who just turned 60. I needed to get her something that was VERY user friendly which usually means it comes at a cost of low quality. I purchased this camera for $80 and was anticipating that the functionality would be limited and the picture quality would be inferior to the 5 Canon digital cameras I've owned in the past few years. I was playing around with the Kodak camera and was surprised to see how easy it was to operate. I think there are many people out there that just want to capture pictures without having to deal with menus and complicated manual settings on digital cameras. My mom was able to take the camera out of the box, turn it on and snap a bunch of pictures using the AUTO setting. She was able to hook it up to her computer and email all of her friends and family recent Easter pictures that she took.
Comments: For $80, you can't complain. This take $150+ camera-like photos. For the not-so-tech-savy moms and dads, this is a safe bet!

Title: No SD Card
Cons: No SD card.
Pros: Compact
Comments: I haven't tried the Camera yet. My brother has a different model easyshare and it is great, but Newegg is selling this one without a memory card. That should have been emphasized.

Title: excellent
Cons: None....for this price.  For those that say the battery door is flimsy, well don't be a caveman and force anything.  It will work just fine and live a long life if you take it easy.
Pros: Very compact, excellent features, takes great pics, software is incredibly easy to use.  Having Video with audio is the best feature IMO.
Comments: SD cards are so cheap and the most universal, I always shop for camera's with SD.

Title: Hum....
Cons:
The butteries’ door is too hard to closer unless you do it very very carefully.
	 	The picture taking quality is NOT HIGH AT ALL!!!!(I compare with my Fuji camera (99$) that bought like 2 years ago the quality…lets say, can use as the wallpaper for a 22’ monitor, its recording quality is not good though) Compare with Fuji, this Kodak one’s picture is SO DAM blur (the details) like a low pixel picture that been resized and fixed…or like everything is been “make-upped” ioi
Pros:
High recording quality, playing is pretty fluent.
Cheap b/c no tax and less than 100$
		Can take clear picture when something is moving (However… see cons.)
Comments:
I feel I am cheated by the brand, because I (I think most people do) think that because Kodak is a company that doing picture business therefore…I bought it….and a little bit disappointed by its picture taking quality which suppose to do.
BUT, for the price, can’t beat it.

Cons:
Annoying to be constantly replacing AA batteries, and buying rechargeable AA's with a charger is an extra $30+
Screen leaves something to be desired when reviewing photos.
Pros:
Lightweight
High Megapixels for the Price
Easy to Use
Comments: We upgraded to this camera from a DX7440 and have no regrets.

Title: excellent buy
Cons: The batteries that came with the camera were dead.
Pros: The ease and simplicity of operation with this camera is great. Takes awesome pictures for a economy camera.
Comments: Ordered it on a Wednesday it arrived Thursday mid day. We were not expecting it for at least three to four days. If this is the turn around time to be expected and the great value we will be ordering again.
